The City of Cape Town has officially approved the Harbour Arch mixed-use development after years of delay. The parcel of foreshore land, spanning 5.3 hectares, was previously owned by Transnet but has since been bought by Amdec for its R14-billion mixed-use development. “Within the context of the burgeoning Cape Town CBD, Harbour Arch occupies a strategic position at the convergence of major access roads, with easy entry points to and from the N1 and N2 highways,” Amdec said. “It is set to be built on a 5.8-hectare site, with 198,000m2 of usable space and six individual towers. “The site will also be home to two new hotels, to be operated by Marriott International, long-standing partners of the Amdec Group and the world’s largest hospitality group. <img class="size-full wp-image-349595 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2.jpg" alt="" width="1657" height="1265" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2.jpg 1657w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2-300x229.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2-768x586.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2-1024x782.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-2-1200x916.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-349593 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-1.jpg" alt="" width="1920" height="706" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-1.jpg 1920w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-1-300x110.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-1-768x282.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Amdec-1-1024x377.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2